  "text": "The LLVM code generation pipeline consists of several key stages that lower IR to machine code. Here are the core files in the sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d repository:\n\n1. **Instruction Selection (SelectionDAGISel)**: Defined in llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SelectionDAGISel.h with implementation in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGISel.cpp. This class is the common base class for SelectionDAG-based instruction selectors, converting LLVM IR to target-specific SelectionDAG nodes.\n\n2. **IR to DAG Translation (SelectionDAGBuilder)**: The SelectionDAGBuilder class is located in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.h (with implementation in SelectionDAGBuilder.cpp). This class implements routines for translating from LLVM IR into SelectionDAG IR, converting IR instructions into DAG nodes.\n\n3. **Instruction Scheduling (ScheduleDAGRRList)**: Implemented in llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp. This class implements a register pressure reduction list scheduler that uses bottom-up and top-down scheduling algorithms.\n\n4. **Register Allocation (RegAllocGreedy)**: Found in llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.cpp and llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.h. This class implements the RAGreedy function pass for greedy register allocation, which allocates registers to virtual registers while minimizing spills.\n\n5. **Machine Function (MachineFunction)**: Defined in llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h with implementation in llvm/lib/CodeGen/MachineFunction.cpp. This class represents a compiled function at the machine level, containing a list of MachineBasicBlock instances and target-specific information about the generated code.\n\nThese five components form the core of LLVM's code generation backend, working together to transform high-level IR into optimized machine code for a specific target architecture."
}

